  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Support Viet Nam organizations in COVID-19 Preparedness and Response for older persons</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The programme works with national partners in 13 cities and provinces to protect older people and their caregivers from the impact of Covid-19. Its activities aim to make care-giving activities in homes more Covid-secure, raise community awareness of the pandemic and prevention measures and strengthen the capacity of local associations for older people to implement safer community activities.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">3.	To strengthen capacity of local Associations of the Elderly (AE) and community-based Intergenerational Self-Help Clubs (ISHC) on COVID-19 prevention, response and recovery intervention by developing of manuals and guidelines and providing training for community personnel, ISHC Board Members and caregivers.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">2.	To raise awareness and communicate on Covid-19 and promote community engagement by developing and distributing related IEC materials to communities, older persons and their caregivers.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1.	To protect older persons and their caregivers from COVID-19 transmission by providing personnel of Social Protection centers, community personnel and caregivers of local Associations of the Elderly (AE) and community-based Intergenerational Self-Help Clubs (ISHC), who are providing social protection and care services at the older persons&apos; homes, in high-risk areas with personal protective equipment (gloves, masks and protective lenses), essential hygiene and health care item (hand sanitizers, thermometers).</narrative>
  </description>
